prime_award_program_activities_funding_t: 0099: N/A;009S: MISCELLANEOUS
prime_award_base_transaction_description: THIS IS AN AWARD FOR TEAMS NEXT A3. THIS REQUIREMENT WILL SUPPORT THE MISSILE DEFENSE AGENCY DEVELOPMENT AND DEPLOYMENT OF THE INTEGRATED, LAYERED MISSILE DEFENSE SYSTEM.
prime_award_naics_description: ENGINEERING SERVICES
subaward_description: THE STATEMENT OF WORK  SUPPORTS THE MISSILE DEFENSE AGENCY'S (MDAS) MISSION TO DEVELOP, TEST, AND FIELD AN INTEGRATED, LAYERED MISSILE DEFENSE SYSTEM (MDS) TO DEFEND THE UNITED STATES (U.S.), ITS DEPLOYED FORCES, ALLIES, AND FRIENDS AGAINST ALL RANGES OF ENEMY BALLISTIC MISSILES IN ALL PHASES OF FLIGHT. THE TYPES OF SUPPORT REQUIRED INCLUDES: 1) ENGINEERING AND TECHNICAL SUPPORT; 2) STUDIES, ANALYSES, AND EVALUATIONS, AND 3) MANAGEMENT AND PROFESSIONAL SERVICES. THE A3 REQUIREMENT SUPPORTS THE MDAS DEVELOPMENT AND DEPLOYMENT OF THE INTEGRATED, LAYERED MDS BY PROVIDING EXPERT, INDEPENDENT ADVICE, ASSESSMENT, ASSISTANCE, DOCUMENTATION, AND RECOMMENDATIONS REGARDING STRATEGIC, TECHNICAL, PROGRAMMATIC, OPERATIONAL, POLICY, AND ORGANIZATIONAL MATTERS. SUPPORT INCLUDES PROVIDING ASSESSMENTS FOR POLICY DEVELOPMENT, ACQUISITION PLANNING, ENGINEERING, AND TESTING.
